      "id": "PopularPost34139",
      "post_content": "Wizards was kind of boasting with this card back then in an article for it not having a mana cost.  \nI didn't dislike the idea of an arcane only being able to be spliced, in fact i really liked it. But this card was the wrong one to consider doing this with. Yes, it kind of allows you to make any Arcane spell you cast to a cantrip. Yet they could have easily given this card a cost of ![1](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=1&type=symbol)![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol) or even ![Blue](/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&name=U&type=symbol). This would have made it much more useful since you could also have used this card the other way round by casting this and splicing others (as with [Reach Through Mists](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reach Through Mists)).  \nHowever, it's still worth using with the [Shoal](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shoal)s nontheless.",
      "posted_by": "Mode",
      "html": "<div class=\"post oddItem\" id=\"PopularPost34139\">\n<span class=\"postContent\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_post\">Wizards was kind of boasting with this card back then in an article for it not having a mana cost.<br/>I didn't dislike the idea of an arcane only being able to be spliced, in fact i really liked it. <u>But</u> this card was the wrong one to consider doing this with. Yes, it kind of allows you to make any Arcane spell you cast to a cantrip. Yet they could have easily given this card a cost of  <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"1\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=1&amp;type=symbol\"/><img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=U&amp;type=symbol\"/> or even <img align=\"absbottom\" alt=\"Blue\" src=\"/Handlers/Image.ashx?size=small&amp;name=U&amp;type=symbol\"/>. This would have made it much more useful since you could also have used this card the other way round by casting this and splicing others (as with <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Reach Through Mists\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Reach Through Mists\">Reach Through Mists</a>).<br/>However, it's still worth using with the <a class=\"autoCard\" data:cardname=\"Shoal\" href=\"/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?name=Shoal\">Shoal</a>s nontheless.</span>\n<div class=\"postDetails\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_postDetails\" style=\"padding-top: 5px;\">\n<div class=\"reportAbuse\">\n<a href=\"http://wizards.custhelp.com/cgi-bin/wizards.cfg/php/enduser/ask.php?p_prods=522,706,739&amp;p_cats=\" id=\"ctl00_ctl00_ctl00_MainContent_SubContent_SubContent_popularPosts_postsRepeater_ctl03_reportAbuseLink\" onclick=\"HandleReportPost(this, '34139'); return false;\">\r\n                                    Report Abuse</a>\u00a0\u00a0\r\n                                \r\n                            </div>\n<div class=