      "id": "PopularPost81638",
      "post_content": "Tsk.  \n  \nPerhaps because Kamigawa came right after [Mirrodin](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=50943) one could theorize that Wizards was trying to limit the power level of cards/strategies. Even still, I think that that's bull. Arcane spells are far from being competent of winning a game (more competent than [Storm Crows](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=83282) and [Air Elementals](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=189884)). They have much room for power level boosts without even thinking of being a top-tier strategy.  \n  \nWith that, this is indeed a thoughtful card in the mechanic. However, this card only works (in an arcane-spell heavy deck) when the deck is at an advantage (even slight) with the opponent. Otherwise, it's as dead as a card can be. I say this because 90% of arcane spells are weak and situational, and the strategy or your life total will crumble when attempting to bend over backwards to splice this onto something (You [Rend Flesh](/Pages/Card/Details.aspx?multiverseid=75259) an ir... [(see all)](javascript:void(0);)",
      "posted_by": "Enchantment_Removal",
